<TITLE> ADB reiterates support for SMEs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com)The Asian Development Bank will continue to assist the development of small and medium enterprises in Bangladesh, according to the Bank's country director. Paul J Heytens, the newly appointed country director, in a meeting on Wednesday at the SME Foundation pledged supports to foster the growth of SMEs, according to a statement by the Foundation. "ADB will increase its support for enhancing the growth of the country's small and medium enterprises (SMEs)," the statement quoted Heytens as saying. The meeting focused on issues like capacity building, women entrepreneurship, poverty elevation and job creation, co-ordination, monitoring system, encouragement and the process of providing assistance and guidance for the SME development and promotion. SME Foundation's chairperson Aftab ul Islam, managing director Momtaz Uddin Ahmed and ADB financial management officer MM Zillur Rahman was attended the meeting. Heytens told the meeting that proper nursing and development of SMEs and upholding women empowerment would help boost income opportunities, strengthen household security, improve living standards, and reduce the risk of unemployment.
